  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I rent a two wheeler in Mumbai?",
  "response": "Renting a two-wheeler in Mumbai can be a convenient way to navigate the city's busy streets. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to rent a two-wheeler in Mumbai:\n\n### 1. **Research Rental Companies**\n   - **Online Search:** Use search engines to find reputable two-wheeler rental companies in Mumbai. Some popular rental services include Vogo, Bounce, and Royal Brothers.\n   - **Apps:** Look for apps dedicated to bike rentals, many of which provide services in Mumbai.\n   - **Local Providers:** You may also find local, smaller rental providers. Check reviews and ratings to ensure reliability.\n\n### 2. **Check Availability and Pricing**\n   - **Browse Options:** Visit the websites or apps of rental companies to browse available models, ranging from scooters to motorcycles.\n   - **Compare Prices:** Look at daily, weekly, and monthly rental charges. Note any additional costs like insurance, fuel, or deposit fees.\n   - **Special Offers:** Some companies may offer discounts or deals, particularly for longer rental periods.\n\n### 3. **Booking the Two-Wheeler**\n   - **Choose the Bike:** Select the bike that fits your needs and budget from the available options.\n   - **Reserve Online:** Most services allow you to book online through their website or mobile app.\n   - **Documents Required:** Typically, you'll need a valid driving license, ID proof (like Aadhar card or passport), and sometimes address proof.\n\n### 4. **Payment**\n   - **Online Payment:** Pay the rental fee online, or if applicable, you might be required to pay a deposit during booking.\n   - **Refund Policy:** Check the rental company\u2019s refund policy in case you need to cancel or reschedule.\n\n### 5. **Pick-Up Instructions**\n   - **Location:** Confirm the pick-up location and time with the rental company. Some providers may have multiple pick-up spots across Mumbai.\n   - **Condition Check:** Upon arrival, inspect the two-wheeler for any damages or issues. Take photos if necessary.\n\n### 6. **Usage and Return**\n   - **Safety:** Wear a helmet and follow all traffic rules.\n   - **Fuel:** Check fuel policy \u2013 some rentals might require you to return the bike with a full tank.\n   - **Return:** Return the bike at the designated location and time. Ensure it\u2019s in the same condition as when you rented it.\n   - **Deposit Refund:** If you paid a deposit, ensure that you get it back post-inspection.\n\n### Tips\n   - **Customer Service:** Choose rental companies known for good customer service.\n   - **Insurance:** Opt for rental services that provide insurance coverage.\n   - **Read Terms:** Carefully read all terms and conditions before renting.\n\nBy following these steps, you can easily rent a two-wheeler in Mumbai and enjoy a convenient mode of transport in the city.",
